# -google: Disables Google integration (such as Drive mounts or OAuth
# components) across various packages.
#
# -dropbox: Removes Dropbox integration plugins from file managers and other
# tools.
#
# -owncloud and -nextcloud: Disables integration with these self-hosted cloud
# platforms, ensuring no sync clients or plugins are built.
#
# -kaccounts: Prevents the compilation of KDE's online account management
# framework, useful if you ever pull in Qt or KDE-based applications.
#
# -geoclue -geolocation: Removes geolocation integration, preventing
# applications from determining your physical location.
#
# -telemetry Disables upstream metrics tracking and background analytics
# reporting to maximize network privacy and eliminate data-collection overhead.
*/* -cloudproviders -google -kaccounts -geoclue -geolocation -telemetry

# - gnome-online-accounts: Disabled to prevent unnecessary cloud service bindings.
*/* -gnome-online-accounts
